- "Average revenue per business" is calculated by dividing the total revenue of a sector by the number of businesses in that sector;
- "Economic prosperity" is often indicated by a high GDP, reflecting the economic health and wealth of an area.

- "blooming like flowers" refers to areas and sectors that are experiencing growth;
- "previous period" refers to the preceding time frame for comparison;
- "number of businesses" and "total number of businesses" are metrics used to measure growth.

- "Top-performing business" refers to the business with the highest annual revenue in the area;
